Section 6: Concrete Error Correction Flow

6.1 Real-World Example: Bubble Correction

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Robot as Liquid Handler
    participant Vision as Camera System
    participant Engine as Correction Engine
    participant Recipe as Recipe Book
    participant RL as RL Policy (Phase 3+)
    participant Human as Technician
    
    Robot->>Vision: Complete aspiration
    Vision->>Engine: Detect bubble (BUBBLE-001)
    Engine->>Recipe: Lookup correction protocol
    Recipe-->>Engine: Return CORRECTION_007
    
    alt Phase 1-2: Deterministic
        Engine->>Robot: Execute: Re-aspirate at 80% speed
        Robot->>Vision: Verify correction
        Vision-->>Engine: Success (bubble cleared)
        Engine->>Recipe: Update success rate: 94% â†’ 95%
    else Phase 3+: Adaptive
        Engine->>RL: Request optimization for current context
        RL-->>Engine: Suggest: 82% speed, +1.8mm depth
        Engine->>Human: Present suggestion for approval
        Human-->>Engine: Approve
        Engine->>Robot: Execute optimized correction
        Robot->>Vision: Verify
        Vision-->>RL: Provide reward signal (+1)
    end
    
    Engine->>Robot: Continue protocol
```

6.2 Performance Metrics Evolution

Metric Current Labs (No Correction) Phase 1 (Recipe Book) Phase 3 (Adaptive) Phase 4 (Optimized)
Mean Time To Repair (MTTR) 5-15 minutes < 10 seconds < 5 seconds < 2 seconds
Technician Interventions/day 8-12 1-2 0.5-1 < 0.1
Protocol Success Rate 85-92% 96-98% 98-99% >99.5%
Throughput Impact -15% from errors +5% +12% +22%

